Level 6

The wall behind you feels a bit further away in this room. And you hear more cries for help.

Tip: You can walk backward by passing `'backward'` as an argument to `walk()`. Same goes for `feel()`, `rescue()` and `attack()`. Archers have a limited attack distance.


╔════════╗
║C @ S aa║
╚════════╝

  > = Stairs
  @ = hellsand (20 HP)
  C = Captive (1 HP)
  S = Thick Sludge (24 HP)
  a = Archer (7 HP)


Warrior Abilities:

  Actions:
  
    warrior.rescue()
      Rescue a captive from his chains (earning 20 points) in given direction (forward by default).
  
    warrior.rest()
      Gain 10% of max health back, but do nothing more.
  
    warrior.attack()
      Attacks a unit in given direction (forward by default).
  
    warrior.walk()
      Move in the given direction (forward by default).
  
  Senses:
  
    warrior.health()
      Returns an integer representing your health.
  
    warrior.feel()
      Returns a Space for the given direction (forward by default).
  

When you're done editing Player.js, run the warriorjs command again.
